## 💳 STRIPE

### Setup
1. stripe.com → Dashboard → Developers → API Keys
2. Use **test keys** (`sk_test_`) during development
3. Rocket: Project Settings → Integrations → Stripe → paste Secret Key
4. Then prompt: "Add a $19/month Pro subscription with Stripe checkout on the pricing page"

### Test Cards
| Card | Result |
|---|---|
| `4242 4242 4242 4242` | Successful payment |
| `4000 0000 0000 9995` | Insufficient funds |
| `4000 0025 0000 3155` | 3D Secure required |
Any future expiry date, any 3-digit CVC.

### Common Stripe Issues
| Issue | Fix |
|---|---|
| "No such customer" | Test/live key mismatch — use matching key environment |
| Payment succeeds but subscription not created | Webhook not received — add endpoint in Stripe dashboard |
| "Invalid API Key" | Re-copy key fresh from Stripe dashboard |
| Card declined in test | Wrong test card — use 4242 4242 4242 4242 |
| Works in preview, fails in production | Still on test keys — switch to live keys for prod |
| Webhook not firing | Add your Netlify production URL to Stripe → Webhooks |

### Webhook Setup (Critical for Subscriptions)
1. Stripe Dashboard → Developers → Webhooks → Add endpoint
2. Endpoint URL: `https://your-production-app.netlify.app/api/webhook`
3. Events to listen for:
   - `customer.subscription.created`
   - `customer.subscription.updated`
   - `customer.subscription.deleted`
   - `invoice.payment_succeeded`
   - `invoice.payment_failed`
4. Copy Webhook Secret → add as env var in Rocket Code View or Netlify dashboard

