## 🔌 CUSTOM API INTEGRATION

### Import Methods
| Method | Use When |
|---|---|
| **cURL** | You have a working cURL command |
| **Postman JSON** | You have a Postman collection export |
| **Swagger/OpenAPI** | API has a spec file (.json or .yaml) |
| **Postman workspace key** | You use Postman workspaces |

### API Troubleshooting
| Problem | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| API not in picker | Import incomplete | Re-open Add APIs, re-import |
| `{{accessToken}}` placeholder | Unmapped variable | Bind to state/env var during setup |
| UI not updating after call | Response not stored | Update "Post API call instructions" to store response |
| 401 Unauthorized | Bad/missing auth header | Add `Bearer <token>` to Authorization header in Pre-call instructions |
| CORS error | API blocks browser requests | Create a Supabase Edge Function proxy |
| Works in preview, fails in prod | Hardcoded localhost URL | Update API base URL to production URL |

### CORS Workaround (Most Advanced Common Issue)
When an external API rejects browser requests, create a Supabase Edge Function as a server-side proxy:
1. Ask Rocket in chat: "Create a Supabase edge function that proxies requests to [API endpoint] and handles CORS"
2. The function runs server-side, bypassing browser CORS restrictions
3. Update API calls in your app to hit the edge function URL instead

