## 🔗 GITHUB INTEGRATION

### Export Setup
1. Project Settings → Integrations → GitHub → authorize
2. Create new repo OR push to existing
3. Click Push → Rocket exports all code

### After Export — Local Development
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo
cd your-repo
npm install
cp .env.example .env.local   # add your real Supabase keys
npm run dev                  # runs at http://localhost:3000
```

### Key Limits
- **One-way only**: Rocket → GitHub. Cannot import back into Rocket.
- **No auto-sync**: Must manually push from Rocket after each major change
- **Two-way sync**: On roadmap, not available yet

